<section class="problem section" id="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-head reveal">
        <h2 class="section-title">
          You're flying blind to most of what happens in your cockpit.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-body reveal">
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Traditional FDM tells you what the aircraft did. Thousands of
            parameters on telemetry, configuration, trends. But it can't tell
            you the why behind them.
          </p>
          <p class="problem-question">
            Was the steep descent with spoilers deployed poor energy management,
            or was ATC keeping them high?
          </p>
          <p class="problem-question">
            Was the long landing a poorly flown approach, or a conscious
            decision to mitigate wake turbulence?
          </p>
          <p>
            Your FDM doesn't know. Reports only tell you what crew notice and
            remember.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="problem-close section-close reveal">
      You already have the data. <span class="problem-emphasis-accent">Flightal gives it context.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    background: var(--bg-bone);
  }
  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 5fr 6fr;
      gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 6rem);
    }
  }
  .problem-head .section-title {
    max-width: 18ch;
  }
  .problem-question {
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-phosphor);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  /* Closer sits full-width below the grid, centered — matches the pattern
     used by the Scenarios and DesignPartners sections. */
  .problem-close {
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-strong);
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
  }
  .problem-emphasis-accent {
    color: var(--accent-phosphor);
  }
</style>
